½ lemon
1 tomato
1 pear
1 packet sweet chilli sauce
1 packet beef strips
1 packet garlic paste
1 bag salad leaves
1 packet roasted peanuts
olive oil
1 packet Roasted Pumpkin
1 sachet Southeast Asian Spice Blend

• Prick a few holes in pumpkin packet
• Microwave until hot and steaming, 3 mins
• Slice lemon into wedges. Chop tomato. Thinly slice pear
• In a bowl, combine sweet chilli, lemon juice and a drizzle of olive oil

• Heat oil in a frying pan over high heat
• Cook beef and spice blend, tossing, until browned, 1-2 mins
• Add a drizzle of oil and garlic pasteand cook until fragrant, 1 min

• Add tomato, pear and salad leaves to sweet chilli dressing. Season and toss
• Plate up salad and pumpkin. Top with beef
• Serve with lemon wedges and sprinkled with peanuts